    <item>
      <title></title>
      <link>https://wilocw.github.io/home/about/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 02 Nov 2018 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>https://wilocw.github.io/home/about/</guid>
      <description>Biography Wil Ward is a Research Associate in the Resources, Infrastructure Systems and Built Environments (RISE) group in the Department of Civil and Structural Engineering at the University of Sheffield. He is working on developing machine learning workflows for the efficient retrofit of residential buildings to increase energy efficiency. Previously, he worked in Physics, Statistics and Computer Science departments, researching physically-informed probabilistic machine learning techniques, in particular Gaussian processes, for solutions to non-linear dynamical problems.</description>
